As for placing &quot;under Satan&quot; in there, then sure.  Go for it.  It's your right to say that if that's what you believe and desire in your heart.  Saying, &quot;under Willy Wonka&quot; though is hardly saying what you believe or truely a desire in your heart.  That is making a mockery of the flag and nation.  However, if you truly do believe that Willy Wonka has the ability to guide this nation, say &quot;under Willy Wonka&quot;.  No matter what you say, please respect and honor the flag which is symbolic of our nation.  That's what saying the pledge is all about.  If all you can do is make a mockery of it, then move to a country you do believe in or don't say the pledge at all.  By saying the pledge with &quot;under god&quot; in it, I believe I pay more respect to this nation and wish it more good will than by omitting it or altering the words.  I honor the flag and the nation more because I'm desiring the protection and guidance of my god whom I believe will make the nation a grander, stronger, better place to live in, and I'm expressing that verbally which shows more conviction in my belief and desire for the nation to be great.  If you are an aethiest, then please don't say &quot;under god&quot; because I know you don't believe in a god and by saying the words you're merely mocking the flag. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13891">Creylin McClellan, Dwarven Warlord</a><BR>
